\section{Bookings}

Teachers can list, upload, and clear bookings for a queue, while any user can
inspect their own booking.
<<[[StayawhileSession]] methods>>=
def list_bookings(self, queue):
  """Return the bookings for [[queue]]."""
  return self._request("GET", self._queue_path(queue, "bookings"))


def upsert_bookings(self, queue, bookings):
  """Upload or update [[bookings]] for [[queue]]."""
  return self._request("POST",
                       self._queue_path(queue, "bookings"),
                       payload=bookings)


def clear_bookings(self, queue):
  """Delete all bookings for [[queue]]."""
  return self._request("DELETE", self._queue_path(queue, "bookings"))


def get_my_booking(self, queue):
  """Return the caller's booking for [[queue]]."""
  return self._request("GET", self._queue_path(queue, "my_booking"))
@

The upload endpoint expects a JSON array.
The CLI should accept either a file path or standard input so that shell pipes
 remain convenient.
<<helper functions>>=
def load_json_input(source):
  """Load JSON from [[source]], or stdin when [[source]] is [[-]]."""
  if source == "-":
    return json.load(sys.stdin)

  with open(source, encoding="utf-8") as input_file:
    return json.load(input_file)
